Description: Rim and round handle sherd of Laconian black-glazed pottery trefoil-mouthed oinochoe; glazed black throughout, save inside of handle; inscription on top of junction of rim and handle.
Curator's comments: For parallels, see an oinochoe from Rhodes in the Louvre, H483 [sic - Stibbe], in Stibbe, 'Laconian Oil Flasks and other Closed Shapes', (2000), p. 60, p. 149, no. C5, fig. 125, pl. 10.3.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 612)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GC.40) (phase 3)
